==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Butylene
<hw>Bu"ty*lene</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Butyl</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Any one of
three metameric hydrocarbons, <chform>C4H8</chform>, of the ethylene
series. They are gaseous or easily liquefiable; -- called also
<altname>butene</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the hypothetical divalent radical
<chform>-(CH2)4-</chform>; -- used in combining forms; <as>as,
<ex>butylene</ex> diamine</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>butyl mercaptan</ent>⟦br⟧
